column5: Well had an invite to a small gathering for a friends brothers prewedding festives.Poker,beers and ufc.The next day we would fish the harbour. Man it was like a scene from grumpie old men.LOL    I thought these guys being local would of had huts but nope,so I ended up standing out in the open,but no pro with -1 temps. This guy had a nice set up.    I marked alot of fish.(probly mostly herring,lines were zipping averywhere) Smacked a very small herring on a half and half,and bumped another fish,but to no avail,no fish.  I have to thank Crappieperchhunter for my new addition.Works great Steve. Even picks up the lure and swivel.Awesome.     Thats probly my last outing for sometime,,,,,,,,,,,,,
good to see you got out fishing  but you should have gone to simcoe the bite was hot
Glad you got out B.  Ya, it does look like Grumpy Old Men  But........ you shoulda been on Simcoe
I have only ever caught perch down there...never really give it much of a shot though. Maybe i should?
Glad it's getting some use Brian. It was a shame having it sitting in my basement collecting dust.
Theres, herring and whities and pike and the odd eye ,so I was told, by an older local that was out there.Had a great chat with him. He,s been fishing that area many a years.
Looks like I place I should add to the list to make sure I get out to this winter.
Was thinking that guys,but was with new friends.
Brian, is there a herring season on Gbay?  I'd just keep them for quick strike rigs in the spring, lol.

Thanks for the call bud!.. fishing in my back yard. BTW.. they only fish there because it's a short distance to stagger back to the parking lot...  Bill... you'd want a hungry pike for these lads..and yes you can keep them. (open all year s25/c12)
Grumpy old men eh, did anyone get their hut pulled around by a truck? Ha. Nice report!
Nice Wayne .. but wouldnt it be easier to walk out than 'taxi' on the skis ?
Long walk to Governors Island Jon!!
Last I read Wayne,you were headed to Simcoe.Sry bud.
Very nice Brian, and Wayne, that's the perfect size bait for spring pike.
I really shouldnt say it will be my last for awhile.I can go after work.Im just not an afternoon bite guy,but if Im going to get any use of that new auger STILL  in the box,I better get use to it.
